canonical:
  title: 早行
  author: 崔匡裕
  language: lzh
  text: 纔聞鷄唱獨開扃羸馬悲嘶萬里亭高角遠聲吹片月一鞭寒彩動殘星風牽踈響過山鴈露濕微光隔水螢誰念異鄕遊子苦香燈幾處照銀屛
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 早行
  author: 崔匡裕
  language: lzh
  text: 纔聞鷄唱獨開扃。羸馬悲嘶萬里亭。高角遠聲吹片月。一鞭寒彩動殘星。風牽踈響過山鴈。露濕微光隔水螢。誰念異鄕遊子苦。香燈幾處照銀屛。
korean:
  title: 조행
  author: 최광유
  language: kor
  text: |-
    닭 우는 소리 듣고 나 혼자 문을 나니
    여윈 말이 구슬피 우네 만리정자(만리길을 떠나는 역정(驛亭))에서
    가락 높은 각소리는 조각달에 멀리 불고
    싸늘한 채찍 그림자는 지는 별을 움직이네
    바람에 끌리는 성긴 메아리는 산을 지나는 기러기
    이슬에 젖은 희미한 빛은 물 건너 반딧불
    뉘라서 생각해 주리 이역 나그네 괴로움
    몇 곳에나 향 피우는 등이 은병을 비추는지
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0150_010_0160&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Early Journey
  author: Choe Kwang-yu
  language: eng
  text: |-
    At the rooster's crow I slip out alone through the gate,
    A gaunt horse whinnies mournfully at the station of ten thousand li.
    The high horn's distant note pierces the fragmented moon,
    A cold whip's shadow stirs the dying stars.
    Wind-drawn sparse echoes drift past geese crossing mountains,
    Dew-dampened faint light divides the fireflies beyond water.
    Who will take pity on this wanderer's suffering in foreign lands?
    How many lanterns burning incense illuminate silver screens back home?
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'station of ten thousand li' (萬里亭) evokes both the vast distance of travel and the traditional relay stations where travelers rested during long journeys.
  - key: ''
    value: The imagery of the moon, stars, geese, and fireflies creates a poignant natural landscape that mirrors the speaker's loneliness and distance from home.
  - key: ''
    value: The final couplet contrasts the vivid sensory details of the journey with the distant memory of home, where loved ones remain unaware of the traveler's hardship.
